==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''geniculatus'' (with bended knee) from ''geniculum'',which is a diminutive of ''genu'', (knee). See the Indo-european route [[genu-]].

===Adjective===
'''geniculate'''

# Bent abruptly, with the structure of a knee. 
# Having kneelike joints; able to bend at an abrupt angle. 

